[Patient] What are some affordable heart-healthy food options I can buy in my neighborhood?
[Educator] Try buying canned beans, frozen vegetables, and whole grains like brown rice for nutritious meals.
[Patient] I have trouble cooking. What can I do?
[Educator] Consider simple recipes like salads, smoothies, or one-pot meals that require minimal cooking skills.
[Patient] How can I afford healthy food on a tight budget?
[Educator] Look into local food assistance programs, farmer's markets, or bulk buying for cost-effective options.
[Patient] I don't have a car to go to the grocery store. What should I do?
[Educator] Check if grocery delivery services or community transportation options are available in your area.
[Patient] Can you recommend some quick and easy heart-healthy snacks?
[Educator] Opt for fresh fruits, nuts, yogurt, or whole grain crackers as convenient and nutritious snack choices.